The paper deals with the problem of self-interference in a multi-user MIMO setup, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields. However, the main focus of the paper is on the information theory aspects of the problem, such as the capacity of the channel and the distribution of the residual self-interference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.COM (Computers and Society).
